Super Eagles duo Victor Osmhen and Wilfred Ndidi closely trail Mohamed Salah and Sadio Mane as Africa’s most prized assets. The latest list was published by the influential CIES Football Observatory academics, that includes a world top 100 led by Kylian Mbappe. On an African scale, Osimhen is fourth and 66th place in the world with a €64m valuation, while Leicester City’s Ndidi sits fifth in Africa, 94th globally with a value of €50m. Leading the continental pack are the likes of Salah and Mane are valued at €145 and €139, as well as Arsenal’s Pepe at €73m.